WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Here I'll tell you a little bit of a story.

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:04.239
So this fall I traveled as a school rep

00:00:04.239 --> 00:00:07.199
for Ambassador Baptist College, the college I went to.

00:00:07.199 --> 00:00:08.560
And as I was traveling around,

00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:10.640
I got to go to many different states

00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:12.199
and to see a lot of different cool things.

00:00:12.199 --> 00:00:14.720
And a lot of times I'd preach a Christian school chapel

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:16.399
or something like that in the morning.

00:00:16.399 --> 00:00:19.079
And a lot of times I'd be done around noon or one o'clock

00:00:19.079 --> 00:00:20.319
after lunch, sometimes there

00:00:20.319 --> 00:00:21.879
at the different Christian schools.

00:00:21.879 --> 00:00:23.500
So I'd have some time to kill.

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:25.219
So I would like to find different things to do.

00:00:25.219 --> 00:00:27.040
So sometimes I would find a hiking trail

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:29.479
and I'd hike up a mountain or something like that.

00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:32.520
And other times I was in more of a bigger city, if you will,

00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:34.240
where a lot of college universities were.

00:00:34.240 --> 00:00:35.500
So it's kind of interesting to go

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:38.479
on different college campuses across the nation.

00:00:38.479 --> 00:00:40.279
We just kind of observe people in different things.

00:00:40.279 --> 00:00:43.080
But something I really enjoy is college football.

00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:45.080
I enjoy watching it on the television.

00:00:45.080 --> 00:00:47.040
And you see all these places on TV,

00:00:47.040 --> 00:00:48.680
but I was able this fall to go

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:50.639
to a lot of different college football stadiums

00:00:50.639 --> 00:00:53.439
and actually see them and actually go out on the fields

00:00:53.439 --> 00:00:54.500
and different things like that.

00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:55.959
So over the course of the fall,

00:00:55.959 --> 00:00:59.000
I got to go to Illinois University's football stadium.

00:00:59.759 --> 00:01:01.880
I got to go by Michigan State University's stadium.

00:01:01.880 --> 00:01:04.400
I got to go by West Virginia, which is my favorite team

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:05.239
in the whole wide world,

00:01:05.239 --> 00:01:06.779
the West Virginia University Mountaineers.

00:01:06.779 --> 00:01:09.239
I got to go by Notre Dame University's stadium.

00:01:09.239 --> 00:01:11.879
I got to go to a whole bunch of different stadiums.

00:01:11.879 --> 00:01:14.559
And one day I was up in Ann Arbor, Michigan.

00:01:14.559 --> 00:01:16.400
So I was like, well, hey, I'm free today.

00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:18.680
Why not, let's check out the big house, as they call it,

00:01:18.680 --> 00:01:21.099
where Michigan University plays college football.

00:01:21.099 --> 00:01:23.239
So I put in directions there on my phone,

00:01:23.239 --> 00:01:25.639
put in directions there to the football stadium.

00:01:25.639 --> 00:01:26.620
So I'm following my directions.

00:01:26.620 --> 00:01:27.559
I have no idea where I'm at.

00:01:27.559 --> 00:01:29.319
I'm just in Ann Arbor, Michigan.

00:01:29.319 --> 00:01:31.919
And I pull up to a stoplight and the light is red.

00:01:31.919 --> 00:01:33.220
It's about rush hour time.

00:01:33.220 --> 00:01:34.720
So traffic was pretty busy.

00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:36.680
So I get there to this red light.

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:39.239
I'm trying to make a left-hand turn here at the light.

00:01:39.239 --> 00:01:40.839
And I'm here at the light.

00:01:40.839 --> 00:01:42.080
And the one thing about this light though

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:44.059
is it doesn't have an arrow on it, a left-hand arrow.

00:01:44.059 --> 00:01:45.959
So those of you who drive know that when you're trying

00:01:45.959 --> 00:01:47.400
to make a left and the light turns green,

00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:49.000
you have to yield to oncoming traffic.

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:50.760
You just can't pull out in front of somebody.

00:01:50.760 --> 00:01:51.800
So the light turns green.

00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:52.959
I'm about ready to go.

00:01:52.959 --> 00:01:54.120
There's all these cars.

00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:56.639
Keep going right by.

00:01:56.639 --> 00:01:57.480
Light turns yellow.

00:01:57.480 --> 00:01:58.300
Light turns red.

00:01:58.300 --> 00:01:59.319
I'm like, are you serious?

00:01:59.319 --> 00:02:02.599
I waited a whole cycle and could not make a left-hand turn.

00:02:02.599 --> 00:02:04.879
So the second cycle, light turns green.

00:02:07.559 --> 00:02:08.559
Steady stream of traffic.

00:02:08.559 --> 00:02:09.720
Again, light turns yellow.

00:02:09.720 --> 00:02:10.600
Light turns red.

00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:12.320
I'm like, are you kidding me?

00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:14.860
I was starting to get a little bit frustrated here.

00:02:14.860 --> 00:02:16.440
Third time, same thing.

00:02:16.440 --> 00:02:17.679
I'm like, are you kidding me?

00:02:17.679 --> 00:02:22.080
They need to put a crazy left-hand turn thing here.

00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:23.960
So by this time, I looked at my rear view mirror

00:02:23.960 --> 00:02:25.880
and I'd presume a student there at the University

00:02:25.880 --> 00:02:26.839
of Michigan, a female.

00:02:26.839 --> 00:02:28.919
She was not very happy with me at this point.

00:02:28.919 --> 00:02:32.199
And I looked at my rear view mirror and she was going,

00:02:32.199 --> 00:02:33.360
she was like yelling at me.

00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:34.679
And I'm like, I can't do anything.

00:02:34.679 --> 00:02:35.880
I'm sorry.

00:02:35.880 --> 00:02:38.539
So finally, on the fourth time, I'm at the light.

00:02:38.539 --> 00:02:41.679
It turns green and two cars go, if I remember right.

00:02:41.679 --> 00:02:42.839
And then I saw something glorious.

00:02:42.839 --> 00:02:44.320
I saw a dump truck.

00:02:44.320 --> 00:02:47.139
Now, dump trucks don't accelerate very fast, you know?

00:02:47.139 --> 00:02:48.479
So I'm like, here's my opportunity.

00:02:48.479 --> 00:02:49.320
Here we go.

00:02:49.320 --> 00:02:50.679
So, and it was plenty safe.

00:02:50.679 --> 00:02:51.559
I saw my opportunity.

00:02:51.559 --> 00:02:53.960
There was a big gap there and I stepped on the gas

00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:56.080
and I made it and actually the car behind me made it.

00:02:56.080 --> 00:02:57.919
And we was able to go through that light.

00:02:57.919 --> 00:02:59.240
And I was able to see the stadium

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:01.360
and have a great rest of my day.

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.119
But if you will, I had to wait

00:03:03.119 --> 00:03:05.800
before I could go through that light.

00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:07.639
But can I say tonight on a Sunday evening

00:03:07.639 --> 00:03:11.360
that you do not have to wait to share the gospel.

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:14.199
You can go and share the gospel even tonight

00:03:14.199 --> 00:03:15.880
right after the service.

00:03:15.880 --> 00:03:17.919
And that's simply the title of the message this evening.

00:03:17.919 --> 00:03:20.820
Go and share the gospel.

00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:23.399
Go and share the gospel.

00:03:23.399 --> 00:03:25.039
So here in Mark chapter number 16,

00:03:25.039 --> 00:03:26.240
to kind of set the context

00:03:26.240 --> 00:03:29.759
to where we'll be picking up our Bible passage tonight.

00:03:29.759 --> 00:03:33.800
Jesus, he has just died for our sins there on the cross.

00:03:33.800 --> 00:03:34.720
You know, he was beaten.

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:36.960
He was, as we heard this morning from Brother Cottle,

00:03:36.960 --> 00:03:40.559
he was crucified there on Calvary.

00:03:40.559 --> 00:03:43.100
And he was buried there in that old borrowed tomb.

00:03:43.100 --> 00:03:44.380
And no doubt at this time,

00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:46.559
his disciples were a little bit distraught.

00:03:46.559 --> 00:03:47.720
The man that they had followed,

00:03:47.720 --> 00:03:48.880
that they thought, you know,

00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:51.720
was gonna be the king is now dead.

00:03:52.720 --> 00:03:56.479
But I'm thankful that Jesus, he didn't stay dead.

00:03:56.479 --> 00:03:58.600
My savior rose again from the dead,

00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:00.199
conquering sin, conquering death.

00:04:00.199 --> 00:04:04.160
And he's alive right now, up in heaven right now.

00:04:04.160 --> 00:04:05.000
But these disciples,

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:08.320
they haven't heard yet that Jesus is alive.

00:04:08.320 --> 00:04:09.399
And that's where we're gonna be picking up

00:04:09.399 --> 00:04:12.360
our Bible account tonight in Mark chapter number 16.

00:04:12.360 --> 00:04:14.000
We'll begin reading in verse number nine,

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:15.880
where the Bible says this.

00:04:15.880 --> 00:04:19.200
Now, when Jesus was risen early the first day of the week,

00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:20.839
he appeared first to Mary Magdalene,

00:04:20.839 --> 00:04:23.000
out of whom he had cast seven devils.

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.880
And she went and told them that had been with him

00:04:25.880 --> 00:04:27.679
as they mourned and wept.

00:04:27.679 --> 00:04:29.679
And they, when they had heard that he was alive

00:04:29.679 --> 00:04:32.239
and had been seen of her, believed not.

00:04:32.239 --> 00:04:33.119
So let's get the picture here.

00:04:33.119 --> 00:04:35.040
We have Jesus, he is now alive.

00:04:35.040 --> 00:04:36.760
He's now risen.

00:04:36.760 --> 00:04:39.880
And he appears first to this lady named Mary Magdalene.

00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:42.079
So no doubt, Mary Magdalene, she's excited now.

00:04:42.079 --> 00:04:44.000
She realizes that Jesus is alive.

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:46.359
So Mary Magdalene runs back to the disciples

00:04:46.359 --> 00:04:47.519
who are gathered together and says,

00:04:47.640 --> 00:04:49.200
hey, disciples, guess what?

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:51.200
Jesus is alive.

00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:52.040
And what does the Bible say?

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:54.480
The Bible says that they believe her not.

00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:55.559
They're probably like, oh, Mary,

00:04:55.559 --> 00:04:57.239
you must've had a crazy dream last night,

00:04:57.239 --> 00:04:58.320
but Jesus, no, he's dead.

00:04:58.320 --> 00:05:00.600
We saw him, he's dead.

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:02.160
They don't believe.

00:05:02.160 --> 00:05:04.559
Look back at verse number 12 here where the Bible says,

00:05:04.559 --> 00:05:07.000
after that, he, speaking of Jesus,

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.040
appeared in another form unto two of them

00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:12.119
as they walked and went into the country.

00:05:12.119 --> 00:05:14.220
And they went and told it unto the residue,

00:05:14.220 --> 00:05:16.920
neither believed they them.

00:05:16.920 --> 00:05:20.200
So Jesus, he appears in another form to two other disciples.

00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:21.279
Now these two other disciples,

00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:23.720
they run back to the disciples who were gathered together,

00:05:23.720 --> 00:05:25.420
say, hey, Jesus is alive.

00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:27.320
Jesus is alive.

00:05:27.320 --> 00:05:32.320
And the disciples again do not believe that Jesus is alive.

00:05:33.040 --> 00:05:34.380
And then look at verse number 14.

00:05:34.380 --> 00:05:36.760
We have Jesus who arrives back on the scene.

00:05:36.760 --> 00:05:39.119
It says, afterward, he, again, speaking of Jesus,

00:05:39.119 --> 00:05:41.640
appeared unto the 11, speaking of the disciples,

00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:44.359
as they sat at meat and upbraided them

00:05:44.359 --> 00:05:47.519
with their unbelief and hardness of heart,

00:05:47.519 --> 00:05:48.679
because they believed not them

00:05:48.679 --> 00:05:51.079
which had seen him after he was risen.

00:05:51.079 --> 00:05:54.239
And he said unto them, go ye into all the world

00:05:54.239 --> 00:05:57.440
and preach the gospel to every creature.

00:05:57.440 --> 00:05:59.720
He that believeth and is baptized shall be saved,

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:01.720
but he that believeth not shall be damned.

00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:03.399
And these signs shall follow them that believe.

00:06:03.399 --> 00:06:05.440
In my name shall I cast out devils.

00:06:05.440 --> 00:06:07.200
They shall speak with new tongues.

00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:08.359
They shall take up serpents.

00:06:08.359 --> 00:06:11.040
And if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them.

00:06:11.040 --> 00:06:13.760
They shall lay hands on the sick and they shall recover.

00:06:13.760 --> 00:06:15.600
So then after the Lord had spoken unto them,

00:06:15.600 --> 00:06:17.480
he was received up into heaven

00:06:17.480 --> 00:06:19.440
and sat on the right hand of God.

00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:23.000
And they went forth and preached everywhere,

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:24.660
the Lord working with them

00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:27.320
and confirming the word with signs following.

00:06:27.320 --> 00:06:28.160
Amen.

00:06:28.160 --> 00:06:28.980
If you would join me for a quick word of prayer,

00:06:28.980 --> 00:06:30.239
then we're gonna jump right into it.

00:06:30.239 --> 00:06:32.040
Father, I sure do love you.

00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:34.000
And I thank you so much for the opportunity

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:35.040
to preach your word tonight.

00:06:35.040 --> 00:06:37.100
Lord, I thank you so much for Fellowship Baptist Church

00:06:37.100 --> 00:06:38.920
and for the man's and just for everything

00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:40.239
that they've done for me personally

00:06:40.239 --> 00:06:41.600
in the DC Gospel Outreach.

00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:43.000
And Lord, I pray now that,

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:44.239
Father, you would speak to our hearts

00:06:44.239 --> 00:06:45.359
and draw us closer to you, Lord.

00:06:45.359 --> 00:06:46.720
My words aren't gonna do anything,

00:06:46.720 --> 00:06:48.559
but I know that your word has the power.

00:06:48.559 --> 00:06:50.160
And God, would you please speak to our hearts

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:51.559
and draw us closer to you?

00:06:51.559 --> 00:06:53.200
And Lord, may we believe your change

00:06:53.200 --> 00:06:55.059
as a result of your word being preached tonight.

00:06:55.059 --> 00:06:55.899
Lord, I love you.

00:06:55.899 --> 00:06:57.380
In Jesus' name I pray.

00:06:57.380 --> 00:06:58.920
Amen.

00:06:58.920 --> 00:06:59.760
Amen.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:00.579
So point number one this evening,

00:07:00.579 --> 00:07:03.679
if you're taking notes is God's commands.

00:07:03.679 --> 00:07:06.600
Point number one this evening, God's commands.

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:08.040
So here, as we already looked at,

00:07:08.040 --> 00:07:10.880
we had Mary Magdalene who came to the disciples

00:07:10.880 --> 00:07:11.920
and they didn't believe her.

00:07:11.920 --> 00:07:13.799
And then we had the two other disciples

00:07:13.799 --> 00:07:15.720
who came to the 11 as they were sat there

00:07:15.720 --> 00:07:17.160
and they didn't believe them.

00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:19.480
And then Jesus, as we read, shows up on the scene

00:07:19.480 --> 00:07:21.519
and he kind of gets into his disciples a little bit.

00:07:21.519 --> 00:07:23.959
Like, hey, like guys, why didn't you believe?

00:07:23.959 --> 00:07:25.679
The Bible says he upbraided them

00:07:25.679 --> 00:07:28.959
with their unbelief and hardness of heart.

00:07:28.959 --> 00:07:31.000
And then Jesus, he kind of pivots from,

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:33.079
hey guys, get with the program a little bit.

00:07:33.079 --> 00:07:34.760
He kind of pivots to giving them

00:07:34.760 --> 00:07:37.600
some very important commands that,

00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:38.839
yes, were applicable to them,

00:07:38.839 --> 00:07:41.839
but is applicable to us today.

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:44.799
So what is the first command that Christ gave

00:07:44.799 --> 00:07:45.640
to his disciples?

00:07:45.640 --> 00:07:48.559
The first command is simply to go.

00:07:48.559 --> 00:07:50.160
To go, it's right there in our texts.

00:07:50.160 --> 00:07:53.540
And he, speaking of Jesus, said unto them,

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:55.920
what's that next word, church?

00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:57.679
What's that next word, church?

00:07:57.679 --> 00:08:00.920
Go, go ye into all the world

00:08:00.920 --> 00:08:03.799
and preach the gospel to every creature.

00:08:03.799 --> 00:08:07.239
Go, it has the idea to move over an area,

00:08:07.239 --> 00:08:10.679
to proceed, to take action.

00:08:10.679 --> 00:08:11.959
It's a simple fact this evening,

00:08:11.959 --> 00:08:13.519
but to go somewhere requires action

00:08:13.519 --> 00:08:17.279
on the part of the person who is to go.

00:08:17.279 --> 00:08:18.799
Now, I have one younger brother.

00:08:18.799 --> 00:08:20.839
He's two and a half years younger than myself.

00:08:20.839 --> 00:08:22.559
And he's actually right now in the Ivory Coast,

00:08:22.559 --> 00:08:24.540
West Africa on a missions internship.

00:08:24.540 --> 00:08:26.059
So if you think of him, pray for him.

00:08:26.059 --> 00:08:28.160
I know he would appreciate that.

00:08:28.160 --> 00:08:30.880
But this was back a little while.

00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:31.720
I think it was, let's see,

00:08:31.720 --> 00:08:33.359
it was last Thanksgiving, I believe.

00:08:33.359 --> 00:08:34.320
And he has a girlfriend.

00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:36.400
She's down in Whitfield, Virginia, a really great girl.

00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:39.840
And we were down there visiting her and her family there.

00:08:39.840 --> 00:08:41.840
And I just happened to be there, if you will.

00:08:41.840 --> 00:08:43.640
And we had a great dinner with the family.

00:08:43.640 --> 00:08:45.400
And afterwards, we went outside.

00:08:45.400 --> 00:08:47.760
They have a bunch of dogs, actually breed dogs.

00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:49.280
And thanks to, they have a bunch of dogs.

00:08:49.280 --> 00:08:50.239
And there was one dog there

00:08:50.239 --> 00:08:52.159
that we were playing fetch with.

00:08:52.159 --> 00:08:54.479
So we took the ball and I'd throw the ball

00:08:54.479 --> 00:08:56.479
and the dog, boy, it loved chasing after that ball,

00:08:56.479 --> 00:08:57.400
would go after it.

00:08:57.400 --> 00:08:58.640
And then it would bring the ball back.

00:08:58.640 --> 00:09:00.400
And the ball's a little bit slobbery by this point.

00:09:00.400 --> 00:09:02.400
And I'm like, do I really wanna pick that ball up?

00:09:02.400 --> 00:09:04.479
Not really, but it's for a dog, so might as well.

00:09:04.479 --> 00:09:06.479
So I'd pick the ball up and I'd throw it again.

00:09:06.479 --> 00:09:07.760
And the dog would chase after it

00:09:07.760 --> 00:09:09.000
and bring it right on back.

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:10.119
And we kept doing it.

00:09:10.119 --> 00:09:12.559
Then they brought out this Nerf gun thing for tennis balls,

00:09:12.559 --> 00:09:13.799
which I didn't even know they made.

00:09:13.799 --> 00:09:15.280
So you put the tennis ball in there,

00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:17.000
you cock the Nerf gun and boom, you'd shoot it

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:18.760
and it'd go about 50 feet in the air.

00:09:18.760 --> 00:09:20.000
There would go off the tennis ball.

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:22.080
And the dog, boy, would just keep running after that ball.

00:09:22.080 --> 00:09:24.880
And we did that for a whole long time.

00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:26.679
But I want you to imagine with me here,

00:09:26.679 --> 00:09:28.619
if we have this dog here,

00:09:28.619 --> 00:09:30.719
if I throw the ball and I say, all right, dog, go get it.

00:09:30.719 --> 00:09:32.119
And the dog just sits there.

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:35.760
Is the ball gonna magically come back to the dog?

00:09:35.760 --> 00:09:38.840
No, it requires action on the part of the dog

00:09:38.840 --> 00:09:41.520
