00:13:55.759 --> 00:13:58.639
to Seventh Days, to some monks, to you name it.

00:13:58.639 --> 00:14:00.119
We've probably seen it out there.

00:14:00.119 --> 00:14:01.859
Everybody trying to get their message across

00:14:01.859 --> 00:14:03.659
or their way to God.

00:14:03.659 --> 00:14:04.499
But I can promise you,

00:14:04.499 --> 00:14:07.699
those ways will not get you anywhere.

00:14:07.699 --> 00:14:10.239
Only the message of the gospel from the Bible

00:14:10.239 --> 00:14:11.679
will get them anywhere.

00:14:11.679 --> 00:14:13.119
My words aren't gonna change anything,

00:14:13.119 --> 00:14:14.979
but the word of God is quick and powerful

00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:16.839
and sharper than any two-edged sword.

00:14:16.859 --> 00:14:20.219
The word of God and the gospel is the message

00:14:20.219 --> 00:14:23.619
that people need to hear.

00:14:23.619 --> 00:14:26.539
And can I say, Christian, don't be ashamed of the gospel.

00:14:26.539 --> 00:14:27.979
So many times we live our lives

00:14:27.979 --> 00:14:29.219
like we're undercover Christians,

00:14:29.219 --> 00:14:31.419
like, oh, I don't want anybody to know that I'm a Christian.

00:14:31.419 --> 00:14:33.159
Or at the workplace, man, if they know I'm a Christian,

00:14:33.159 --> 00:14:35.339
man, some things could happen to me.

00:14:35.339 --> 00:14:37.000
But hey, don't be ashamed of the gospel.

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:41.439
Instead, embrace the glorious message of the gospel.

00:14:41.439 --> 00:14:42.939
Again, this fall, I was out traveling

00:14:42.939 --> 00:14:45.899
and one time I was going to Virginia Beach, Virginia,

00:14:45.899 --> 00:14:47.879
not terribly far from here.

00:14:47.879 --> 00:14:49.119
And I was gonna be at some churches there

00:14:49.119 --> 00:14:50.759
in the Virginia Beach area.

00:14:50.759 --> 00:14:53.239
And so I was looking online, I did all my bookings

00:14:53.239 --> 00:14:55.599
as far as scheduling things and finding my hotels

00:14:55.599 --> 00:14:56.559
and all that, I did that myself.

00:14:56.559 --> 00:15:00.199
So I was looking on my phone for a hotel to stay at

00:15:00.199 --> 00:15:02.439
and I was finding, because I was during the fall time,

00:15:02.439 --> 00:15:03.279
so it was kind of cooler

00:15:03.279 --> 00:15:04.819
and not a whole lot of people were there for the beach.

00:15:04.819 --> 00:15:07.239
So all the hotels, the rooms were ridiculously cheap.

00:15:07.239 --> 00:15:08.559
I mean, like, I got a really nice hotel.

00:15:08.559 --> 00:15:10.839
I think it was like 65 bucks with tax and everything.

00:15:10.839 --> 00:15:12.479
So I mean, it was a great deal.

00:15:12.479 --> 00:15:15.279
So anyway, so I checked into my hotel

00:15:15.279 --> 00:15:16.579
and there was the boardwalk there.

00:15:16.579 --> 00:15:17.979
I think it was about 50 degrees or so.

00:15:17.979 --> 00:15:18.899
So I mean, it was still nice.

00:15:18.899 --> 00:15:19.739
You could still walk out

00:15:19.739 --> 00:15:20.779
and you weren't freezing or anything.

00:15:20.779 --> 00:15:22.619
So I was walking down the boardwalk

00:15:22.619 --> 00:15:24.059
and I think I called my parents a little bit,

00:15:24.059 --> 00:15:25.179
was just talking with them.

00:15:25.179 --> 00:15:26.779
So I was kind of walking down the boardwalk

00:15:26.779 --> 00:15:28.859
and sure enough, it got to be about eight o'clock

00:15:28.859 --> 00:15:29.699
at night or so.

00:15:29.699 --> 00:15:30.939
And I hadn't eaten dinner yet

00:15:30.939 --> 00:15:32.419
because I'd been on the road and then checked in

00:15:32.419 --> 00:15:34.059
and called my parents and walked a little bit.

00:15:34.059 --> 00:15:35.539
So my stomach was growling.

00:15:35.539 --> 00:15:37.219
I'm like, boy, I am hungry.

00:15:37.219 --> 00:15:38.459
I am ready for some food.

00:15:38.459 --> 00:15:39.659
So I pulled out my phone,

00:15:39.659 --> 00:15:41.979
I looked at fast food restaurants near me.

00:15:41.979 --> 00:15:43.739
And so I think there was a Wendy's over there

00:15:43.739 --> 00:15:44.959
and then there was a Dairy Queen over there.

00:15:44.959 --> 00:15:46.319
I was like, huh, I haven't had Dairy Queen

00:15:46.319 --> 00:15:47.239
for a little while.

00:15:47.239 --> 00:15:48.259
So I'd been on the road a lot.

00:15:48.259 --> 00:15:50.659
So pretty much all I was eating was fast food things

00:15:50.659 --> 00:15:51.719
and things of that nature,

00:15:51.719 --> 00:15:52.559
but I hadn't had Dairy Queen.

00:15:52.559 --> 00:15:54.039
So I'm like, I'll eat the Dairy Queen.

00:15:54.039 --> 00:15:56.000
It was like, I think 0.8 miles away or something

00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:57.839
kind of on the opposite end of the boardwalk.

00:15:57.839 --> 00:15:59.019
So I'm like, ah, it's not too far.

00:15:59.019 --> 00:16:00.439
I can walk that.

00:16:00.439 --> 00:16:02.039
So it took me 20 minutes or however long

00:16:02.039 --> 00:16:03.039
and I got down there.

00:16:03.039 --> 00:16:03.919
And the Dairy Queen,

00:16:03.919 --> 00:16:06.279
it was like an outside style Dairy Queen

00:16:06.279 --> 00:16:07.399
where you couldn't eat inside,

00:16:07.399 --> 00:16:09.679
but they had like where you would order at the window.

00:16:09.679 --> 00:16:11.439
Then they would give your food back at the window

00:16:11.439 --> 00:16:13.179
and you would sit out at different picnic tables

00:16:13.179 --> 00:16:14.939
or wherever you wanted to eat it.

00:16:14.939 --> 00:16:16.459
So I was there, there was a little bit of line.

00:16:16.459 --> 00:16:17.899
It was, they were getting close to closing

00:16:17.899 --> 00:16:18.739
about an hour or so.

00:16:18.739 --> 00:16:20.899
So things, they were kind of starting to slow down

00:16:20.899 --> 00:16:21.819
and there was a little bit of a line.

00:16:21.819 --> 00:16:23.199
There was about six folks in front of me.

00:16:23.199 --> 00:16:25.219
So I waited a little bit and waited some more,

00:16:25.219 --> 00:16:26.539
waited some more.

00:16:26.539 --> 00:16:28.859
And finally it was about my time to go order.

00:16:28.859 --> 00:16:31.000
And I was coming up to the window

00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:32.979
and there was a ruckus behind me

00:16:32.979 --> 00:16:35.059
just as I was starting to order.

00:16:35.059 --> 00:16:35.899
And there was this guy,

00:16:35.899 --> 00:16:37.419
I actually never saw the guy,

00:16:37.419 --> 00:16:40.219
but he was going around and he was yelling.

00:16:40.219 --> 00:16:42.279
He was yelling, Jesus is dead.

00:16:42.279 --> 00:16:44.519
Jesus said, don't you believe what the Bible's lie.

00:16:44.519 --> 00:16:46.479
I mean, just carrying on and saying things

00:16:46.479 --> 00:16:49.119
that should not be repeated and just going on and on.

00:16:49.119 --> 00:16:50.919
So I finished ordering and I turned around

00:16:50.919 --> 00:16:51.879
and he was already gone.

00:16:51.879 --> 00:16:53.199
I have no idea where he ended up,

00:16:53.199 --> 00:16:55.439
but he had obviously walked on by.

00:16:55.439 --> 00:16:57.879
I tell you, it broke my heart to see this man proclaiming.

00:16:57.879 --> 00:16:59.959
I mean, he didn't care who already, he was yelling.

00:16:59.959 --> 00:17:02.239
I don't know if he was on drugs or alcohol, I don't know,

00:17:02.239 --> 00:17:05.759
but he was proclaiming aloud the message that Jesus is dead.

00:17:05.759 --> 00:17:08.459
But could I say tonight that if a lost man

00:17:08.459 --> 00:17:10.919
can walk the streets of Virginia Beach, Virginia

00:17:10.919 --> 00:17:13.199
and proclaim that Jesus is dead,

00:17:13.199 --> 00:17:16.039
I think it's time for us as Christians to preach,

00:17:16.039 --> 00:17:17.599
if you will, to proclaim aloud the message

00:17:17.599 --> 00:17:19.479
that no, Jesus, he's alive.

00:17:19.479 --> 00:17:21.359
He is the only way to heaven.

00:17:21.359 --> 00:17:23.819
And let's share the gospel with a world

00:17:23.819 --> 00:17:28.599
that desperately needs the message of the gospel.

00:17:28.599 --> 00:17:30.000
Romans 1 16 says,

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:32.519
for I am not ashamed of the gospel of Christ,

00:17:32.519 --> 00:17:34.279
for it is the power of God unto salvation

00:17:34.279 --> 00:17:35.719
to everyone that believeth,

00:17:35.719 --> 00:17:38.819
to the Jew first and also to the Greek.

00:17:38.819 --> 00:17:41.879
Don't be ashamed of the gospel, embrace it.

00:17:41.879 --> 00:17:44.859
Make your life all about the gospel.

00:17:44.859 --> 00:17:46.179
Hudson Taylor had a great quote.

00:17:46.179 --> 00:17:47.500
He said, the great commission

00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:49.819
is not an option to be considered.

00:17:49.819 --> 00:17:52.099
