00:28:38.520 --> 00:28:40.679
In that survey, only 6% of people,

00:28:40.679 --> 00:28:42.000
this is a survey taken here in America,

00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:45.119
only 6% of people in America

00:28:45.119 --> 00:28:48.239
said that that was the Bible way to heaven, 6%.

00:28:48.239 --> 00:28:51.520
Here in America, where we got churches everywhere,

00:28:51.520 --> 00:28:56.520
6% of people, less than one in 10 people in America

00:28:57.359 --> 00:28:59.700
said that that was the Bible way to heaven.

00:28:59.700 --> 00:29:01.799
So that kind of got me thinking a little bit.

00:29:01.799 --> 00:29:02.719
So I did a Google search.

00:29:02.719 --> 00:29:06.279
I said, how many people a day in the United States die?

00:29:06.279 --> 00:29:07.320
What a Google search, right?

00:29:07.359 --> 00:29:09.640
And I was like, how many people in the United States die a day?

00:29:09.640 --> 00:29:10.919
And in a rough Google search,

00:29:10.919 --> 00:29:12.479
you'll get a few varying numbers,

00:29:12.479 --> 00:29:13.399
but generally speaking,

00:29:13.399 --> 00:29:16.440
people will have it around 8,400 people, roughly speaking.

00:29:16.440 --> 00:29:19.640
The one that I got right here is 8,460 people each day

00:29:19.640 --> 00:29:21.320
die in the United States.

00:29:21.320 --> 00:29:23.520
So if we take, we'll round up to 10%.

00:29:23.520 --> 00:29:25.399
Let's just, for sake of illustration tonight,

00:29:25.399 --> 00:29:27.839
say that 10% of people in America are saved,

00:29:27.839 --> 00:29:29.440
which again, I know that poll could be skewed,

00:29:29.440 --> 00:29:31.359
it could be up or down, I understand that.

00:29:31.359 --> 00:29:34.760
Let's just say 10% of people in America are saved,

00:29:35.000 --> 00:29:37.399
with 8,460 people each day dying.

00:29:37.399 --> 00:29:40.399
If you do the math on that, if that stat is true,

00:29:40.399 --> 00:29:43.359
508 people each day who die here in America

00:29:43.359 --> 00:29:45.320
are saved and go into heaven.

00:29:45.320 --> 00:29:46.479
But if that stat is true,

00:29:46.479 --> 00:29:51.440
7,952 people each day who die are lost

00:29:51.440 --> 00:29:53.419
and going to spend an eternity

00:29:53.419 --> 00:29:55.820
in a godless place called hell.

00:29:55.820 --> 00:29:56.839
Let that number sink in.

00:29:56.839 --> 00:29:59.359
Nearly, here in America, we're not talking the world,

00:29:59.359 --> 00:30:00.520
we're talking America.

00:30:00.520 --> 00:30:07.520
Nearly 8,000 people each day who die are going to spend to a godless place called hell.

00:30:07.520 --> 00:30:09.520
That ought to break our hearts as Christians.

00:30:09.520 --> 00:30:12.520
To think that that many people are dying each and every day,

00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:15.520
and they don't know Jesus as their Savior.

00:30:15.520 --> 00:30:18.520
If that doesn't motivate you to share the gospel, friend,

00:30:18.520 --> 00:30:20.520
can I say this? I don't know what will.

00:30:20.520 --> 00:30:23.520
It's time that we as Christians take Christ's command seriously

00:30:23.520 --> 00:30:29.520
to go into all the world to preach the gospel to every creature.

00:30:29.520 --> 00:30:32.520
Oh, that we would have a church here at Fellowship Baptist Church

00:30:32.520 --> 00:30:34.520
that takes the gospel seriously.

00:30:34.520 --> 00:30:37.520
That goes out and shares the gospel with their friends, with their family,

00:30:37.520 --> 00:30:40.520
with their co-workers, with everybody they come in contact with.

00:30:40.520 --> 00:30:46.520
The best message that anybody could hear, the message of the gospel.

00:30:46.520 --> 00:30:48.520
I'll close with one more illustration.

00:30:48.520 --> 00:30:50.520
I was recently coming back on the metro one evening.

00:30:50.520 --> 00:30:52.520
And to be honest with you, I was a little bit tired.

00:30:52.520 --> 00:30:54.520
I was exhausted from the long day out.

00:30:54.520 --> 00:30:56.520
And I was sitting there at the metro.

00:30:56.520 --> 00:30:57.520
I was probably playing on my phone,

00:30:57.520 --> 00:30:59.520
maybe looking at some sports highlights or something like that.

00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:01.520
And there was a man that got on the metro.

00:31:01.520 --> 00:31:03.520
He looked a little bit disheveled.

00:31:03.520 --> 00:31:06.520
And he could tell he was a little bit down and out.

00:31:06.520 --> 00:31:08.520
But kind of as he got in, I didn't think anything of it.

00:31:08.520 --> 00:31:10.520
And kind of the Holy Spirit just started pricking my heart.

00:31:10.520 --> 00:31:12.520
Hey, talk to him about the Lord. Hey, give him a tract.

00:31:12.520 --> 00:31:14.520
And I was like, Lord, I really don't feel like it right now.

00:31:14.520 --> 00:31:16.520
I'm tired. I just want to go back home.

00:31:16.520 --> 00:31:19.520
But the Holy Spirit was like, hey, hey, talk to him.

00:31:19.520 --> 00:31:20.520
So I was like, yes, sir, Lord.

00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:22.520
So I got up and I had a gospel tract on me.

00:31:22.520 --> 00:31:25.520
And I said, hey, sir, could I give you something that talks about God's love for you?

00:31:25.520 --> 00:31:27.520
Whatever I said, I'm not exactly sure.

00:31:27.520 --> 00:31:28.520
And that man looked up at me.

00:31:28.520 --> 00:31:30.520
And as sincere as he could, he said, huh.

00:31:30.520 --> 00:31:32.520
He said, I didn't grow up Christian.

00:31:32.520 --> 00:31:33.520
I didn't grow up going to church.

00:31:33.520 --> 00:31:38.520
But recently I've been thinking about Christianity and about God.

00:31:38.520 --> 00:31:39.520
Whoa.

00:31:39.520 --> 00:31:40.520
I was not expecting that response.

00:31:40.520 --> 00:31:42.520
To be honest with you, I was expecting him to say, no, I'm good.

00:31:42.520 --> 00:31:44.520
Thank you. Go on, man.

00:31:44.520 --> 00:31:46.520
But he was open to the gospel.

00:31:46.520 --> 00:31:49.520
Could there be some people like that in your lives?

00:31:49.520 --> 00:31:51.520
That God might just put them right in front of you

00:31:51.520 --> 00:31:53.520
that are looking for something different?

00:31:53.520 --> 00:31:56.520
I can promise you that, yes, there's pleasure and sin for a season.

00:31:56.520 --> 00:32:00.520
But the world's philosophies and ways, they're not going to do anything for a person.

00:32:00.520 --> 00:32:05.520
Only the gospel and a personal relationship with Jesus can bring hope and peace to a person's life.

00:32:05.520 --> 00:32:09.520
Could God put some people in your life this week, tomorrow at work,

00:32:09.520 --> 00:32:11.520
that you're able to share the gospel with?

00:32:11.520 --> 00:32:13.520
Why not pray about it?

00:32:13.520 --> 00:32:16.520
Christian, are you sharing the gospel?

00:32:16.520 --> 00:32:19.520
Do you have a burden for the lost?

00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:25.520
Why not tonight make a choice that you're going to be a gospel Christian and share the gospel?

00:32:25.520 --> 00:32:28.520
If you would bow your heads and close your eyes, I'm going to ask Pastor Mann to come.

00:32:28.520 --> 00:32:32.520
I'm going to pray here in a second and then let him take the invitation, however the Lord leads.

00:32:32.520 --> 00:32:34.520
But, Father, we sure do love you.

00:32:34.520 --> 00:32:36.520
And thank you so much again for the opportunity to preach tonight.

00:32:36.520 --> 00:32:38.520
Lord, I thank you for your word.

00:32:38.520 --> 00:32:42.520
I thank you just for dying on the cross, Lord, to pay for my sins, to give us the message of the gospel.

00:32:42.520 --> 00:32:46.520
And, Father, help each one of us to be faithful to take the gospel message,

00:32:46.520 --> 00:32:50.520
whether that be through a gospel track, through talking to somebody about the Lord.

00:32:50.520 --> 00:32:55.520
God, I pray that you help each one of us to be gospel Christians and to simply go and share the gospel.

00:32:55.520 --> 00:32:58.520
Lord, take control of the invitation. It's yours. In Jesus' name we pray.

